@page "/docs/quick-start"

<PageTitle>Quick Start — BlazorMotion</PageTitle>

<div class="breadcrumb">Docs / <span>Quick Start</span></div>
<h1>Quick Start</h1>
<p>Get BlazorMotion running in your Blazor WebAssembly app in under 5 minutes.</p>

<h2>Installation</h2>
<p>Add the <code>BlazorMotion</code> project reference (or NuGet package when published):</p>
<pre><code>&lt;PackageReference Include="BlazorMotion" Version="1.*" /&gt;</code></pre>

<h2>Register services</h2>
<p>In <code>Program.cs</code>:</p>
<pre><code>using BlazorMotion.Extensions;

builder.Services.AddBlazorMotion();</code></pre>

<h2>Add global imports</h2>
<p>In <code>_Imports.razor</code>:</p>
<pre><code>@@using BlazorMotion.Components
@@using BlazorMotion.Models
@@using BlazorMotion.Services</code></pre>

<h2>Your first animation</h2>
<p>Replace any HTML element with a <code>&lt;Motion&gt;</code> component and add animation props:</p>
<pre><code>&lt;Motion Tag="div"
        Initial="@@(new AnimationProps { Opacity = 0, Y = 20 })"
        Animate="@@(new AnimationProps  { Opacity = 1, Y = 0 })"
        Transition="@@(TransitionConfig.BounceSpring(0.5, 0.3))"
        Class="my-box"&gt;
    Hello, BlazorMotion!
&lt;/Motion&gt;</code></pre>

<div class="demo-area">
    <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;align-items:center;gap:1.25rem;">
        <Motion @key="_replayKey" 
                Class="demo-box"
                Initial="@(new AnimationProps { Opacity = 0, Scale = 0.5 })"
                Animate="@(new AnimationProps { Opacity = 1, Scale = 1 })"
                Transition="@(TransitionConfig.BounceSpring(0.6, 0.4))">
            ✨
        </Motion>
        <button class="demo-button" @onclick="Replay">&#9654; Replay</button>
    </div>
</div>

@code {
    private int _replayKey = 0;

    private void Replay() => _replayKey++;
}

